The paper deals with finding Nash equilibrium in continuous games, which is a topic in game theory (cs.GT). The paper also uses deep learning techniques to approximate the equilibrium, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also involves optimization algorithms, which is a topic in numerical analysis (cs.NE) and control theory (cs.SY).
